NBAuthenticator, NBAuthenticatorCodes
public class SimpleNBAuthenticator
extends java.lang.Object
implements NBAuthenticator

Simple northbound authenticator.

Documentation note: The terms "user" and "client identifier" are used interchangably in the following discussion and are meant to refer to the clientID field of the northbound API internal Hello message. This field represents the nominal user/client login identification name. Any consistency checks of the clientID field with respect to transport elements (e.g., SSL X509 peer certificate data) must already have been performed prior to use of the simple northbound authenticator.

This authenticator provides extensible client authentication through configuration-defined module definitions used by per-client authentication rules. The configuration data is contained in a JSON-formatted file specified via the northbound server's "SIMPLE_AUTHENTICATOR_JSON_PATH" configuration parameter. The JSON-formatted configuration file must define a single root JsonNode object which may contain the following fields:

  • "auth_modules": Defines the named authentication modules (these names will be used to set the "authenType" field of the northbound API internal AuthenRequest message elements). The value associated with this field must be a JsonNode object. Each field of this JsonNode object is a module definition, with the field names establishing the unique set of module names and the field values defining the implementation class and initialization data for the modules. If no modules are defined then users may only be enabled or disabled by name as the simple northbound authenticator does not have any predefined modules.
  • "users": Defines the client identifier database and the per-user authentication requirements. The value associated with this field must be a JsonNode object. Each field of this JsonNode object is a client entry, with the field names establishing the unique set of client identifiers and the field values defining the authentication requirement rules for that client identifier. If no user entries are defined, then all authentication requests will return InvalidUser.
  • "failed_rule_disable": This optional element determines if a client authentication rule specification (at configuration time) causes the client login identifier to be disabled. If set false, the offending rule is ignored and all other client rules are unaffected. Note that a user with an empty authentication rule list is by default a disabled user entry (AuthenFail).

The field value for a user entry may be one of the following:

  • A boolean value indicating the authenticateClient() return code. If true, Accept is returned. if false, AuthenFail is returned. No modules are used.
  • An integer value specifying the authenticateClient() return code. No modules are used.
  • A JsonNode object specifying a single authentication rule for the user.
  • A JsonNode array of JsonNode objects specifying a set of authentication rules for the user.

If one or more authentication rules are specified for a user, the initial authenticateClient() call will try each in turn. The first rule returning either an Accept or Request value will be used for the remainder of the authenticateClient() authentication protocol exchange calls. Note, however, that the clientTerminated() notification call will be made to all rules defined for the user.

An authentication rule is a JsonNode object containing at least one of the following fields (collectively defining at least one authentication rule element):

  • "required_auth": this field specifies the required authentication elements for this rule. All required elements must return an Accept code from the authenticateClient() method for a rule to authenticate a user. Similarly, for a rule to return a Request code, all required elements must return either Accept or Request. The value of the field is either a JsonNode object or an array of JsonNode object containing authentication rule element fields.
  • "optional_auth": this field specifies the optional authentication elements for this rule. At least one optional element must return an Accept code from the authenticateClient() method for a rule to authenticate a user. Note: Care should be taken in ordering the optional authentication elements because the first element that returns an Accept code will skip evaluation of the remaining elements, which may have unexpected consequences if a required element causes further protocol exchanges. The value of the field is either a JsonNode object or an array of JsonNode objects containing authentication rule element fields.

An authentication rule element is a field in a JsonNode object where the name idetnifies an authentication module. The module will then be asked to create the element given the (arbitrary) JsonNode field value. Consult the individual module implementation classes to determine what parameters are required for the module.
